    "is_good_patch": false,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Replace magic number with symbolic constant in SMTC gap offset calculation\n\n### Summary\nIn the NR MAC layer, the function `extract_gap_offset_from_smtc` uses a hardcoded value `10` when calculating gap offsets from SMTC (Synchronization Signal/Monitoring Timing Configuration) structures. This magic number makes the code harder to understand and maintain.\n\nThis change introduces a symbolic constant `SMTC_PERIODICITY_MIN` with value `10` to replace the magic number, improving code clarity and maintainability.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_gNB/nr_mac_gNB.h`: Added `#define SMTC_PERIODICITY_MIN 10`\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_gNB/config.c`: Replaced hardcoded `10` with `SMTC_PERIODICITY_MIN` in gap offset calculation\n\n### Reproduction Steps\n1. Configure a gNB with SMTC settings that require gap offset calculations\n2. Observe that the current implementation uses a hardcoded value `10` in the modulo operation\n3. After applying the fix, the same calculation uses the named constant `SMTC_PERIODICITY_MIN`\n\nThe change is functionally equivalent but makes the intent of the code clearer for future maintenance.\n"
}